content.title: Salesforce SOQL Query Python
content.visibleText:
# Salesforce connection
sf = Salesforce(username=username, password=password, security_token=security_token)

# SOQL query
query = 'SELECT Id, Name FROM Account LIMIT 10'

# Execute the query
results = sf.query(query)

# Print results
for record in results['records']:
 print(record['Id'], record['Name'])

Key Points:
• Username, Password, and Security Token: You need to replace 'your_username', 'your_password', and 'your_security_token' with your actual Salesforce credentials. The security token is typically required when accessing Salesforce from an untrusted network.
• Query: The `query` variable holds your SOQL query string. You can modify it to fit your specific data retrieval needs.
